```

Creates a commit with full analysis and syncs to configured integrations.

### Skip Analysis

```bash
ai-commit "docs: update README" --no-analysis
```

Creates a commit without running AI analysis (faster for documentation changes).

### Skip Push

```bash
ai-commit "fix: resolve bug" --no-push
```

Creates a commit but doesn't push to remote (useful when you want to review before pushing).

### Analyze Only (No Commit)

```bash
ai-commit --analyze-only
```

Runs analysis on staged changes without creating a commit. Useful for reviewing code quality before committing.

### Dry Run

```bash
ai-commit "test: add tests" --dry-run
```

Shows what would happen without actually making any changes. Great for testing or understanding the workflow.

### Verbose Mode

```bash
